# Virtual environments: 
1. create a virtual environment using VENV ( comes with python) , or CONDA - creates a folder in the same place and it will have a name too which has been given as aurgument. 
  syntax: python -m venv tutorial-env 
  this creates 800 something files in the folder, under 3 sub folders. Include, Lib and Scripts. 
  A copy of python interpreter is also kept here
2. Activating the virtual environment. This can be done by running a bash script which has been preloaded in Scripts folder.
  syntax: tutorial-env\Scripts\activate
3. Security error based on Execution Policy 135170. give access to run .ps1 files which are power shell files 
  syntax: Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser 
  The possible values of -ExecutionPolicy are RemoteSigned, Restricted and unrestricted.
4. Use PIP ( Preferred Installer Program) to add packages that you need just for this specific project.   

